post_text:
Sharyland ISD is committed to making sure that students have access to healthy nutritious meals during Virtual Learning. That is why the Sharyland ISD Child Nutrition Program is teaming up with our Transportation department to introduce our new ‚ÄúFresh Express Buses‚Äù Bus stop meals distribution program. This program is intended for the student who does not have personal transportation to get to their home campus to pick up curb side meals. These meals will be charged in the same manner as in-school meals would be. The schools buses will be serving Meals on the bus routes of Jensen, Garza, Martinez and Bentsen Elementary, every Monday and Wednesday. Meal Service Distribution times are 10:45a.m.-11:45a.m. and 12:00p.m -1:00 p.m. Just bring a Sharyland ISD student ID number to receive your meals and check the bus route that is closest to you!

Click here for more information:

https://bit.ly/2Z0iw0L

SHARYLAND ISD Athletic Participation/Extra-Curricular Physical Requirements for 2020-2021

Dear Parents, due to COVID-19, the SISD school board has voted to accept the 2019-2020 UIL physical for the 2020-2021 school year. However, a current medical history form is still required for this school year.

Also, incoming 7th graders, those new to the district and/or those that did not participate in UIL activities during the 2019-20 school year will be required to get a physical for the 2020-21 school year.

Please see link for other requirements for UIL athletic participation/extra-curricular activity.

https://bit.ly/3ftNBiL

Congratulations to the Sharyland ISD 2020 AP Students and Teachers!

Sharyland ISD had 744 students participate in the College Board AP program this year and our students received the following awards: 85 AP Scholars, 27 AP Scholars with Honor, 61 AP Scholars with Distinction and 14 National AP Scholars!

Our 2020 National AP Scholars are: Lois Baldado, Melissa Cantu, Dylan DuCharme, Robert Freeman, Jadon Geathers, Mauricio Gonzalez, Jorge Guerra, Ryan Knobel, Juan Angel Luera, Juan Antonio Luera, Norberto Manzanares, Gared Ramirez, Gabriel Sanchez, and Christian Trevino.

SISD Community,

Please adhere to the Child Nutrition Meal Distribution UPDATE!

Bentsen Elementary will NO longer be a distribution open site. Effective today, please be redirected to either Sharyland High School or Pioneer High School for grab and go meals.

Wednesday, July 8th: 10 total meals for 5 days (11:00 am ‚Äì 1:00 pm)
Friday, July 10th: 14 total meals for 7 days (10:00 am ‚Äì 1:00 pm)
This progressive approach is designed to provide meals up to July 19th, thus allowing SISD to temporarily close the meal distribution program for deep cleaning and to prepare facilities for the upcoming school year. The program is scheduled to resume on July 27th.

Thank you for your continued support.

Friday, July 10th: 14 total meals for 7 days (10:00 am ‚Äì 1:00 pm)
This progressive approach is designed to provide meals up to July 19th, thus allowing SISD to temporarily close the meal distribution program for deep cleaning and to prepare facilities for the upcoming school year. The program is scheduled to resume on July 27th.

Thank you for your continued support.

The Sharyland ISD Board of Trustees approved the purchase of 52 walkthrough temperature scanners. These scanners will be installed at each campus and district facilities to safely and effectively screen all students and staff before entry into our facilities. This purchase is part of an ongoing effort to promote safety across the district, and serve as one of the many safety precautions in place to combat COVID-19 in the Fall. Sharyland ISD will continue to refine guidelines and procedures as information is made available by federal, state, and local agencies. The safety of our students and staff is, and will continue to be, our number one priority.

post_text:
Jerilyn ‚ÄúAbby‚Äù Peralez is a 4-year letter winner in wrestling. She is a 4-time Regional qualifier, a 2-time district champion. In 2020 she qualified to the State Wrestling Tournament in the 95 lb. division. She is also the current SHS Girls MVP in Wrestling.

In addition to wrestling, Jerilyn is also a 3-year letter winner in Cross Country and a 2-year letter winner in Track and Field. She is also a 3-year Regional Qualifier in Cross Country and qualified to the State Cross Country Meet in 2019. Jerilyn has the distinct honor of qualifying to the State Tournament in two sports. She has certainly been a major contributor to three sports here at Sharyland High School.

Today, Jerilyn signed a National "Letter of Intent" to participate in Women's Wrestling for Dixie State University, an NCAA Division II school located in St. George, Utah.

post_text:
Karla ‚ÄúIzzy‚Äù Garza is a 4-year letter winner in Track and Field. She is a 3-time Area Qualifier and 2-time Regional qualifier. She finished in 5th place at the 5A Region IV Meet in 2019. She was also the District 31-5A, and Area 31/32 5A pole vault champion in 2019. Karla also holds the Sharyland High school record in the pole vault with a clearing height of 10‚Äô4‚Äù. She set this record as a Junior in 2019.

Karla is also a 3-year letter winner in Girls Basketball. She was selected to the 31-5A All-District Team in 2020. Academically, Karla will graduate with a GPA of 3.51 and is ranked 77 in a graduating class of 382. She has been a major contributor to the success of our Girls Track and Field and Girls Basketball programs.

Today, Karla signed a National "Letter of Intent" to participate in Women's Track for the University of Texas Rio Grande Valley, an NCAA Division I school located in Edinburg, Tx.

Maialen Erana is a Senior on the Sharyland High School Women‚Äôs Golf Team. She is a 4 year letter, was an individual Regional Qualifier her freshman year, and has made a State appearance once. Maialen is a very hard worker. When she leaves our school practice, she practices more at the McAllen Country Club or Palm View Golf course. She has always strived to be the best that she can be.

Throughout high school, Maialen has 5 top 10 Varsity finishes, made 3rd Team All-District her Sophomore year, 2nd Team All-District her Junior year and 1st Team All-District her Senior year.

Maialen has also excelled in the classroom during her time at Sharyland High School. She is ranked in the top 16% of her class and is a great example of what a ‚ÄúStudent Athlete‚Äù is.

Maialen signed an NLI to participate in Golf for Concordia University in Austin, Texas. Concordia University is an NCAA Division III college and is in the American Southwest Conference.

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May.

The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Sharyland High School students got to explore and listen to survivor testimonies of the Holocaust through an immersive live musical performance by South Texas College's Music Department titled, Hate, Hope, and Healing: Exploring the Holocaust Through Music.

Students learned how the actions of the Holocaust came to be, the experiences of those imprisoned, and the liberation by the Allies, which coincides with the 75th anniversary of the end of World War II this year.
